<h4 id="android-rom">Android ROM</h4>

<p>æ—¢ç„¶æåˆ° Android å°±ä¸å¾—ä¸ææ Android ROM</p>

<p>ROM çš„æœ¬ä¹‰å®é™…ä¸Šæ˜¯åªè¯»å†…å­˜ï¼š</p>

<p><strong>Read-only memory</strong> (ROM) is a class of storage medium used in computers and other electronic devices. Data stored in ROM can only be modified slowly, with difficulty, or not at all, so it is <strong>mainly used to distribute firmware (å›ºä»¶)</strong> (software that is very closely tied to specific hardware, and unlikely to need frequent updates).</p>

<p>ROM åœ¨å‘å±•çš„è¿‡ç¨‹ä¸­ä¸æ–­è¿›åŒ–ï¼Œä»åªè¯»æ¼”å˜æˆäº†å¯ç¼–ç¨‹å¯æ“¦é™¤ï¼Œå¹¶æœ€ç»ˆæ¼”åŒ–æˆäº† Flash</p>

